Note:
compiler/frontend/primitives/types/construction.runa
Type Construction Primitives

This module provides fundamental type construction operations for all Runa primitive types.

Key features and capabilities:
- Factory methods for creating primitive type instances
- Default value construction for all types
- Copy and clone operations for immutable types
- Builder patterns for complex type construction
- Memory-efficient construction techniques
- Type-safe construction with validation
- Performance-optimized creation routines
- Zero-allocation construction where possible
- Integration with compiler type system
- Error handling for invalid construction
- Thread-safe construction operations
- Resource management for constructed objects
:End Note

Import "dev/debug/errors/core" as Errors
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout" as Layout
Import "text/string/builder" as StringBuilder
Import "data/collections/core/list" as ListOps
Import "data/collections/core/map" as MapOps

Note: =====================================================================
Note: CONSTRUCTION RESULT TYPES
Note: =====================================================================

Type called "ConstructionResult":
    success as Boolean                         Note: Whether construction succeeded
    constructed_value as Optional[String]      Note: String representation of constructed value
    value_type as String                       Note: Type of the constructed value
    memory_allocated as Optional[Integer]      Note: Memory used for construction
    error_message as Optional[String]          Note: Error details if construction failed

Type called "ConstructionOptions":
    use_default_values as Boolean              Note: Fill missing fields with defaults
    validate_during_construction as Boolean    Note: Validate while constructing
    memory_optimization as String              Note: none, minimal, aggressive
    error_handling as String                   Note: strict, lenient, ignore
    locale_settings as Optional[Dictionary[String, String]] Note: Locale-specific construction

Type called "TypeBuilder":
    target_type as String                      Note: Type being constructed
    field_values as Dictionary[String, String] Note: Field name to value mapping
    validation_rules as List[String]           Note: Validation rules to apply
    construction_options as ConstructionOptions Note: Construction configuration

Note: =====================================================================
Note: PRIMITIVE VALUE CONSTRUCTION
Note: =====================================================================

Process called "construct_integer" that takes value as Optional[String], default_value as Optional[Integer] returns ConstructionResult:
    Note: Construct integer from string or use default
    Note: Handles various integer formats (decimal, hex, octal, binary)
    Note: Validates range and format during construction
    Note: Uses default if value is null or invalid (when specified)
    
    Let result be ConstructionResult.new()
    Set result.value_type to "Integer"
    Set result.success to false
    
    If value is None:
        If default_value is not None:
            Set result.constructed_value to Some(default_value.unwrap().to_string())
            Set result.success to true
            Set result.memory_allocated to Some(4)
            Return result
        Otherwise:
            Set result.error_message to Some("No value provided and no default specified")
            Return result
    
    Let input_str be value.unwrap()
    Let parsed_value be parse_integer_from_string(input_str)
    
    If parsed_value is not None:
        Set result.constructed_value to Some(parsed_value.unwrap().to_string())
        Set result.success to true
        Set result.memory_allocated to Some(4)
    Otherwise:
        If default_value is not None:
            Set result.constructed_value to Some(default_value.unwrap().to_string())
            Set result.success to true
            Set result.memory_allocated to Some(4)
        Otherwise:
            Set result.error_message to Some("Invalid integer format: " joined with input_str)
    
    Return result

Process called "construct_float" that takes value as Optional[String], default_value as Optional[Float], precision as Optional[Integer] returns ConstructionResult:
    Note: Construct floating-point number from string or use default
    Note: Supports scientific notation and special values (inf, nan)
    Note: Precision parameter controls decimal precision
    Note: Handles locale-specific decimal separators
    
    Let result be ConstructionResult.new()
    Set result.value_type to "Float"
    Set result.success to false
    
    If value is None:
        If default_value is not None:
            Set result.constructed_value to Some(default_value.unwrap().to_string())
            Set result.success to true
            Set result.memory_allocated to Some(8)
            Return result
        Otherwise:
            Set result.error_message to Some("No value provided and no default specified")
            Return result
    
    Let input_str be value.unwrap()
    Let parsed_value be parse_float_from_string(input_str, precision)
    
    If parsed_value is not None:
        Set result.constructed_value to Some(parsed_value.unwrap().to_string())
        Set result.success to true
        Set result.memory_allocated to Some(8)
    Otherwise:
        If default_value is not None:
            Set result.constructed_value to Some(default_value.unwrap().to_string())
            Set result.success to true
            Set result.memory_allocated to Some(8)
        Otherwise:
            Set result.error_message to Some("Invalid float format: " joined with input_str)
    
    Return result

